NPM()                                                                    NPM()

NNAAMMEE
       nnppmm - Run an npm command

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc npm [options] <npm-command> [npm-command-args]

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              print usage information

       Supports all npm commands, the most commonly used are:

       iinnssttaallll
              install   a  package  from  the  StrongLoop  registry,  or  from
              npmjs.org if a supported version of the package does not exist

       llss     list packages with their support status

       uuppddaattee update packages to latest

